Brijssel mr. Richard Souchelle
In answer to yd of 17 curtt. have rec. fres letters from H.C. so urgens for acceptingl
tris draughts, that I intend to accept 2 more, of which did one this morning, the other
is inst now presented, shall find also acceptance, butt for the £100- de draw for warner
I'il delay till I see him, for I must be rid of those kinde of dealings
yett I nssure you I could do no more then what I have don, & I am consident you would
have don no more yd. self, to do any freind whre soever any kindness, the worst
of all is, that H.M is also by Jt. engaged, hure I can not with donone lett hy
bills returne, this makes mee att mj inots end for this mony on all sides & redrae
for london is much sispected att present, & on you is ernely bad att 2 son for 2
vso, brings proffitt ven low, yett what shall I do, to help my freindes I must pass
the pickes, so have drawne on you £150- flemish this day att 2vso pay able
